Subject: [PATCH] flang: build intrinsic modules under cross when host-runnable

The cross-compiled flang is sometimes host-runnable (e.g. macOS x86_64 binary
on arm64 via Rosetta), so allow opting in to the module_files build under
CMAKE_CROSSCOMPILING via FLANG_BUILD_INTRINSIC_MODULES_CROSS.
---
 flang/tools/f18/CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/flang/tools/f18/CMakeLists.txt b/flang/tools/f18/CMakeLists.txt
index aaaaaaaaaaaa1..bbbbbbbbbbbbb 100644
--- a/flang/tools/f18/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/flang/tools/f18/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -53,7 +53,7 @@ set(module_objects "")
 # If CMAKE_CROSSCOMPILING, then the newly built flang executable was
 # cross compiled, and thus can't be executed on the build system and thus
 # can't be used for generating module files.
-if (NOT CMAKE_CROSSCOMPILING)
+if (NOT CMAKE_CROSSCOMPILING OR FLANG_BUILD_INTRINSIC_MODULES_CROSS)
   foreach(filename ${MODULES})
     set(depends "")
     set(opts "")
